# Entity Relationship Diagram

## Overview

The Entity Relationship (ER) Diagram illustrates the database design of the **A Comprehensive Measure of Well-Being (HDI Prediction System)**. It defines the entities, attributes, primary keys, foreign keys, and relationships required for storing user information, prediction inputs, machine learning models, datasets, and prediction results.

---

## Objective

- Design the database architecture.
- Define entities and relationships.
- Organize HDI prediction data efficiently.
- Improve data consistency.

---

## Entities

- User
- Country
- HDI Input Data
- ML Model
- HDI Prediction
- Dataset
- Visualization Report
- Session

---

## Relationships

- User → HDI Input Data (1:M)
- Country → HDI Input Data (1:M)
- HDI Input Data → HDI Prediction (1:1)
- ML Model → HDI Prediction (1:M)
- HDI Prediction → Visualization Report (1:M)
- Dataset → ML Model (1:M)
- User → Session (1:M)

---

## Tools Used

- Draw.io / Lucidchart / ERD Tool
- Markdown
- GitHub

---

## Outcome

Designed a complete ER Diagram representing the database structure of the HDI Prediction System. The diagram provides a clear understanding of entity relationships and supports efficient application development.

---

## Result

The ER Diagram serves as the foundation for implementing the HDI Prediction System database, ensuring organized data management and scalable machine learning application development.
